1
00:01:08,400 --> 00:01:09,963
[Episode 3: See You Tomorrow]

2
00:01:11,592 --> 00:01:13,353
Can I borrow an umbrella?

3
00:01:22,359 --> 00:01:23,840
Hop on.

4
00:01:23,840 --> 00:01:25,159
Why?

5
00:01:25,159 --> 00:01:26,825
Help me with the umbrella.

6
00:01:28,040 --> 00:01:29,939
Just drizzle.

7
00:01:30,720 --> 00:01:32,505
Just drizzle.

8
00:01:32,505 --> 00:01:33,599
Please,

9
00:01:33,599 --> 00:01:35,519
Classmate Drizzle.

10
00:01:35,519 --> 00:01:36,799
Please,

11
00:01:36,799 --> 00:01:38,838
Mr. Drizzle.

12
00:01:55,400 --> 00:01:56,599
Are you an idiot?

13
00:01:56,599 --> 00:01:58,490
You can't even hold an umbrella!

14
00:02:00,885 --> 00:02:02,800
I'm sorry.

15
00:02:02,800 --> 00:02:04,117
Give it to me.

16
00:02:07,080 --> 00:02:09,160
This way you won't get wet.

17
00:02:09,160 --> 00:02:10,960
I'm already wet.

18
00:02:10,960 --> 00:02:13,737
It's okay. It'll be fine
when the sun comes out.

19
00:02:15,040 --> 00:02:16,520
Thank you.

20
00:02:16,520 --> 00:02:19,257
Thank me with your class notes.

21
00:02:20,960 --> 00:02:22,590
Hold on tight.

22
00:02:29,040 --> 00:02:30,995
Hey. We're going downhill.

23
00:02:31,759 --> 00:02:33,691
You're such a coward.

24
00:02:34,440 --> 00:02:36,120
Because of inertia,

25
00:02:36,120 --> 00:02:37,840
when the combined external force is zero,

26
00:02:37,840 --> 00:02:40,041
an object has a constant velocity.

27
00:03:09,840 --> 00:03:11,159
Come in.

28
00:03:11,159 --> 00:03:12,551
Excuse me.

29
00:03:20,719 --> 00:03:22,520
What do you want?
I only agreed to lend an umbrella.

30
00:03:22,520 --> 00:03:23,720
I thought you agreed to help.

31
00:03:23,720 --> 00:03:24,800
Get out.

32
00:03:24,800 --> 00:03:26,639
Can I pay you for help?

33
00:03:26,639 --> 00:03:28,013
Now.

34
00:03:28,759 --> 00:03:30,639
Mom doesn't cook as well as before.

35
00:03:30,639 --> 00:03:32,759
So I ask you, beg you...

36
00:03:32,759 --> 00:03:34,012
Now.

37
00:03:39,719 --> 00:03:42,040
The dumplings are heavily seasoned.

38
00:03:42,040 --> 00:03:43,320
She's well-aware,

39
00:03:43,320 --> 00:03:45,440
but unwilling to admit it.

40
00:03:45,440 --> 00:03:47,250
Your filling is...

41
00:03:47,250 --> 00:03:48,840
not bad.

42
00:03:48,840 --> 00:03:51,287
So I want you to teach me how to season

43
00:03:51,287 --> 00:03:53,635
and improve her recipe.

44
00:03:54,850 --> 00:03:56,520
2:1

45
00:03:56,520 --> 00:03:58,545
or more?

46
00:04:34,840 --> 00:04:36,257
Only once.

47
00:04:40,760 --> 00:04:43,199
My mom also makes seafood filling.

48
00:04:43,199 --> 00:04:45,519
Seafood needs light seasoning.

49
00:04:45,519 --> 00:04:47,800
Auntie over-seasons it,
which overpowers the dish.

50
00:04:47,800 --> 00:04:49,759
Not much salt.

51
00:04:49,759 --> 00:04:51,399
Shellfish are naturally salty.

52
00:04:51,399 --> 00:04:54,458
Add less salt than usual.

53
00:04:54,458 --> 00:04:55,879
Try it first.

54
00:04:55,879 --> 00:04:57,160
Sugar?

55
00:04:57,160 --> 00:04:58,680
It boosts umami.

56
00:04:58,680 --> 00:05:00,810
Lard is added to enhance the aroma?

57
00:05:00,810 --> 00:05:02,079
Yes.

58
00:05:02,079 --> 00:05:03,120
It forms an oily film

59
00:05:03,120 --> 00:05:06,049
to keep umami and moisture of the filling.

60
00:05:07,120 --> 00:05:08,800
Wait for 10 min

61
00:05:08,800 --> 00:05:11,160
to make it absorb fully.

62
00:05:11,160 --> 00:05:12,360
You came at the right time.

63
00:05:12,360 --> 00:05:13,519
The dough rises.

64
00:05:13,519 --> 00:05:15,402
Intended for breakfast.

65
00:05:21,480 --> 00:05:22,907
Let me do it.

66
00:05:38,400 --> 00:05:40,050
You can put it in now.

67
00:05:40,050 --> 00:05:41,069
Okay.

68
00:06:02,400 --> 00:06:03,643
It's good.

69
00:06:03,643 --> 00:06:05,211
Just a bit dry.

70
00:06:12,586 --> 00:06:13,639
The filling is too oily.

71
00:06:13,639 --> 00:06:16,240
Melted lard sinks to the bottom,

72
00:06:16,240 --> 00:06:18,556
while solidified lard is easier to mix,

73
00:06:18,556 --> 00:06:19,560
right?

74
00:06:19,560 --> 00:06:20,709
Right.

75
00:06:45,560 --> 00:06:47,439
It's getting late. I have to go.

76
00:06:47,439 --> 00:06:48,800
I'll come again tomorrow night.

77
00:06:48,800 --> 00:06:50,120
- I only help you...
- Thank you, Mr. Xiang.

78
00:06:50,120 --> 00:06:51,651
Goodbye, Mr. Xiang.

79
00:06:54,080 --> 00:06:55,623
Once.

80
00:07:11,752 --> 00:07:13,171
This is it.

81
00:07:17,600 --> 00:07:18,895
Thank you.

82
00:07:19,959 --> 00:07:21,346
You're welcome.

83
00:07:26,040 --> 00:07:28,839
You should go.
I need to write down my inspiration.

84
00:07:28,839 --> 00:07:30,639
All of a sudden?

85
00:07:30,639 --> 00:07:32,319
It's still raining.

86
00:07:38,959 --> 00:07:40,382
Bye.

87
00:08:20,679 --> 00:08:22,655
You still keep this umbrella?

88
00:08:23,760 --> 00:08:24,959
For you.

89
00:08:24,959 --> 00:08:26,309
Needn't return it.

90
00:08:48,679 --> 00:08:50,237
Not that umbrella.

91
00:08:51,680 --> 00:08:53,084
I bought one.

92
00:08:58,759 --> 00:08:59,799
Your umbrella.

93
00:08:59,799 --> 00:09:01,620
Class notes.

94
00:09:32,720 --> 00:09:34,463
I'll bring the food.

95
00:10:03,800 --> 00:10:05,923
The chopsticks are clean.

96
00:10:15,840 --> 00:10:17,268
Let's eat.

97
00:10:22,919 --> 00:10:24,260
Here.

98
00:10:36,560 --> 00:10:38,258
Grandma, you eat.

99
00:10:49,320 --> 00:10:51,120
It took some time

100
00:10:51,120 --> 00:10:52,919
to finish my recent notes.

101
00:10:52,919 --> 00:10:54,120
Not too long.

102
00:10:54,120 --> 00:10:55,524
Thanks.

103
00:11:17,200 --> 00:11:18,360
<i>Too crowded.</i>

104
00:11:18,360 --> 00:11:20,240
<i>My dad and his secretary are too busy</i>

105
00:11:20,240 --> 00:11:22,686
<i>to line up and buy tickets for me.</i>

106
00:12:13,480 --> 00:12:15,034
Excuse me.

107
00:12:27,320 --> 00:12:29,459
I thought you wouldn't come.

108
00:12:39,069 --> 00:12:42,089
<i>Xiang Nan Feng, what the hell?</i>

109
00:13:11,040 --> 00:13:12,797
Grandma, be careful.

110
00:13:19,077 --> 00:13:20,560
I'm going to the restroom.

111
00:13:20,560 --> 00:13:22,240
- To the restroom.
- Okay.

112
00:13:22,240 --> 00:13:23,783
Grandma, be careful.

113
00:13:32,399 --> 00:13:33,742
Is it good?

114
00:13:35,279 --> 00:13:36,975
Quite funny.

115
00:13:37,880 --> 00:13:40,596
Watching a movie with someone's grandma.

116
00:13:40,596 --> 00:13:42,360
She's down recently.

117
00:13:42,360 --> 00:13:44,044
I want to cheer her up.

118
00:13:51,000 --> 00:13:53,187
<i>The chopsticks are clean.</i>

119
00:13:57,600 --> 00:13:59,072
What about you?

120
00:13:59,879 --> 00:14:01,376
Me?

121
00:14:06,639 --> 00:14:07,880
<i>Did you hear?</i>

122
00:14:07,880 --> 00:14:09,818
<i>Xiang Nan Feng smells like poop.</i>

123
00:14:09,818 --> 00:14:11,960
<i>Because he fertilizes every day.</i>

124
00:14:11,960 --> 00:14:14,157
<i>- It stinks.
- Disgusting.</i>

125
00:14:19,000 --> 00:14:20,600
She was sound asleep.

126
00:14:20,600 --> 00:14:22,286
Can't be mad at you.

127
00:14:23,039 --> 00:14:24,320
And

128
00:14:24,320 --> 00:14:25,880
it doesn't stink at all.

129
00:14:25,880 --> 00:14:27,159
Really?

130
00:14:27,159 --> 00:14:29,720
A sunbathed odor.

131
00:14:29,720 --> 00:14:31,157
It smells good.

132
00:14:36,120 --> 00:14:37,440
Bye, then.

133
00:14:37,440 --> 00:14:40,200
- Bye, Grandma.
- Yeah. Bye.

134
00:14:40,200 --> 00:14:41,456
Bye.

135
00:15:11,840 --> 00:15:13,200
I'm going back first.

136
00:15:13,200 --> 00:15:14,360
I'm leaving now.

137
00:15:14,360 --> 00:15:15,720
- Okay.
- Yeah.

138
00:15:15,720 --> 00:15:17,747
- Bye, Grandma.
- Yeah.

139
00:15:20,399 --> 00:15:22,059
I have something to tell you.

140
00:15:26,840 --> 00:15:29,240
Actually I've been thinking these days

141
00:15:29,240 --> 00:15:31,120
that we're no longer kids.

142
00:15:31,120 --> 00:15:32,399
Let the past be past.

143
00:15:32,399 --> 00:15:34,159
Time to move on.

144
00:15:34,159 --> 00:15:36,519
I pay you and you help me,

145
00:15:36,519 --> 00:15:38,674
each gets what he needs. Isn't that good?

146
00:15:41,320 --> 00:15:43,279
Money does no harm.

147
00:15:43,279 --> 00:15:45,796
You unilaterally broke up with me.

148
00:15:49,879 --> 00:15:51,279
But you didn't refuse.

149
00:15:51,279 --> 00:15:53,120
Trying to stop someone who's decided to leave

150
00:15:53,120 --> 00:15:54,331
is like arguing about

151
00:15:54,331 --> 00:15:55,920
whether something has happened.

152
00:15:55,920 --> 00:15:57,312
It's meaningless

153
00:15:58,960 --> 00:16:00,523
and very...

154
00:16:00,523 --> 00:16:02,145
embarrassing.

155
00:16:08,159 --> 00:16:09,769
Anything else?

156
00:16:33,879 --> 00:16:36,360
<i>The producer and I just read</i>

157
00:16:36,360 --> 00:16:38,279
<i>the revised first three episodes in one breath.</i>

158
00:16:38,279 --> 00:16:39,600
<i>They're amazing!</i>

159
00:16:39,600 --> 00:16:41,200
<i>We look forward to the next part.</i>

160
00:16:41,200 --> 00:16:42,320
<i>But, Mr. Xiang,</i>

161
00:16:42,320 --> 00:16:45,360
<i>are you inspired by the ex?</i>

162
00:16:45,360 --> 00:16:46,491
<i>No.</i>

163
00:16:48,320 --> 00:16:50,288
Nothing to tell me?

164
00:16:52,840 --> 00:16:54,980
I was actually happy today.

165
00:16:55,720 --> 00:16:58,000
Not that I'm unhappy now.

166
00:16:58,000 --> 00:16:59,707
But that when I see you...

167
00:17:02,240 --> 00:17:03,784
Idiot.

168
00:17:22,120 --> 00:17:23,571
Ren Xi Zhou.

169
00:17:28,400 --> 00:17:29,867
Ren Xi Zhou!
